{"title":"The Crusher is Reincarnated as Mondraker’s Shimano-Powered 150mm Enduro eBike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/the-crusher-is-reincarnated-as-mondrakers-shimano-powered-150mm-enduro-ebike/","date":1694700000000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1600\" height=\"1067\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher ebike 150mm 29er shimano ep801 enduro emtb\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801.jpg 1600w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>For 2024, Mondraker is honing its eBike craft: hot on the heels of the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/mondraker-neat-e-mtbs-blend-light-weight-w-big-ambitions/\" target=\"_blank\">all-new lightweight NEAT eMTB</a> is the reinstated Crusher. Like the 2018 incarnation, the Crusher runs 150mm rear wheel travel supported by Mondraker’s ZERO suspension platform. Only, in 2024, it rocks up on a complete 29″ wheelset.</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don’t Mondraker already have a 150mm travel enduro eMTB with 29″ wheels? Isn’t that the Crafty? </p>\n\n\n\n<p>Yes, and yes. The 2024 Crusher runs the very same geometry and kinematic as the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/mondraker-crafty-xr-ltd-bosch-performance-line-cx-race-motor/\" target=\"_blank\">Bosch-powered Crafty</a>. However, in place of the Bosch Performance Line CX motor is the latest EP801 motor from Shimano. Aside from their engine rooms, there really is very little that sets them apart.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer-800x600.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher emtb enduro ebike shimano ep801\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer-800x600.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer-297x223.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer-120x90.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer-768x576.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer-1536x1152.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-150mm-travel-enduro-ebmtb-shimano-ep801-closer.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Mondraker Crusher eMTB</h2>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Bike: 2024 Mondraker Crusher</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Intention: E-Enduro</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fork Travel: 160mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Rear Wheel Travel: 150mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Frame Material: Carbon front triangle, aluminum swingarm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Motor: Shimano EP801</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Battery Capacity: 720 Wh</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Starting Price: $8,699 USD // £6,299 // € 6.999</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"275\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry-800x275.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher geometry\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry-800x275.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry-297x102.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry-120x41.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry-768x264.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry-1536x527.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-enduro-ebike-geometry.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Geometrically, the Mondraker Crusher is very similar to the Mondraker Crafty. Available in sizes S-XL, all have generous 455mm chainstays, and a 25mm BB drop, with reasonably short seat tubes across the board (450mm in L). The most notable difference in geometry is the slightly slacker head angle of 65° – this is 65.5° on the Bosch-powered Crafty. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>As such, the Crusher has the slightly longer wheelbase, too; 1285mm on the Large. All have an effective seat tube angle of 76°.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher shimano ep801 motor 85 nm torque\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-forward-geometry-shimano-ep801-motor.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"534\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode-800x534.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher shimano ep801 motor walk mode\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode-800x534.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode-1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-Mondraker-Crusher-ebike-shimano-ep801-motor-walk-mode.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Shimano EP801 Drive Unit powering the Crusher has a maximum torque of 85 Nm and weighs a claimed 2.7 kg. Meanwhile. the Bosch Performance Line CX motor found on the Mondraker Crafty has the same maximum torque output, but is a little heavier at a claimed 2.9 kg. It is the Crafty that has the bigger battery, however, at 750 Wh versus the Crusher’s 720 Wh battery.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DU-EP801_Drive_Unit_4-Large-e1657548381298.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"481\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DU-EP801_Drive_Unit_4-Large-e1657548381298-800x481.jpeg\" alt=\"shimano ep801 motor drive unit\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DU-EP801_Drive_Unit_4-Large-e1657548381298-800x481.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DU-EP801_Drive_Unit_4-Large-e1657548381298-297x179.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DU-EP801_Drive_Unit_4-Large-e1657548381298-120x72.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DU-EP801_Drive_Unit_4-Large-e1657548381298-768x462.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/DU-EP801_Drive_Unit_4-Large-e1657548381298.jpeg 1013w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Pricing &amp; Availability</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The 2024 Shimano-powered Mondraker Crusher eMTB is available in three build models, all of which are appropriately spec’d with 38mm stanchion forks, and 4-piston brakes with 203/200mm rotors. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level-800x533.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level-800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level-768x511.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level-1536x1022.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level-720x480.jpg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-model-grey-entry-level.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>First up is the Crusher, period. Available only in a Nimbus Grey / Vortex Grey / Bronze colorway only, this entry-level model retails at the most reachable price point of $8,699 USD. It benefits from a FOX 38 Performance fork with the FIT damper, a FOX Float X Performance shock, a SRAM GX Eagle chain set, their mineral oil DB8 brakes, an ONOFF Pija dropper seatpost (125-200mm of travel, size-dependent) and a Maxxis Minion DHF/DHR II pairing – both at 2.6″ wide in the EXO+ casing.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"541\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue-800x541.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher r\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue-800x541.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue-297x201.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue-120x81.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue-768x519.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue-1536x1039.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusherr-r-model-blue.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Middle of the road is the Crusher R model. In its only available Denim Blue / Navy Blue / Racing Silver colorway, it goes for $9,699 USD. Upgrades include an Ohlins RXF 38 M.2 fork, Ohlins TTX 22 M air shock, a SRAM X01 Eagle chain set, and SRAM Bronze Stealth Brakes.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"525\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range-800x525.jpg\" alt=\"mondraker crusher rr\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range-800x525.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range-297x195.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range-120x79.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range-768x504.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range-1536x1007.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/mondraker-crusher-rr-model-top-of-the-range.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Topping the range is the Crusher RR, yours for just $11,399 USD. It too gets the Ohlins suspension, but the major highlight of this build is the Shimano Deore XT Di2 electronic group, boasting the FREE SHIFT function – <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-emtb-autoshift-freeshift-stuns-powered-by-linkglide-xt-di2-review/\" target=\"_blank\">see Cory’s take on that</a>. It also rolls up on a Mavic E-Deemax S carbon wheelset. Pick it up in the Red Carbon / Black / Racing Silver colorway only (pictured throughout).</p>\n\n\n\n<p>See international pricing for the 2024 Mondraker Crusher E-Enduro Bike below. More details on spec and availability can be found on the Mondraker website.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"159\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide-800x159.jpg\" alt=\"2024 mondraker crusher international pricing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide-800x159.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide-297x59.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide-120x24.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide-768x153.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide-1536x305.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/09/2024-mondraker-crusher-enduro-ebike-pricing-worldwide.jpg 1600w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://mondraker.com/\" target=\"_blank\">mondraker.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/the-crusher-is-reincarnated-as-mondrakers-shimano-powered-150mm-enduro-ebike/\">The Crusher is Reincarnated as Mondraker’s Shimano-Powered 150mm Enduro eBike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f338b81cb2a113a666e6648f627be5c73d9ebb49936755fb74c090897c15d7f1","category":"Cycling"}